Dow drops nearly 125 points on losses in Merck, Home Depot shares
Shares of Merck and Home Depot are seeing declines Monday afternoon, dragging the Dow Jones Industrial Average into negative territory. Shares of Merck MRK, -0.70% and Home Depot HD, -0.65% have contributed to the index's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, -0.51% was most recently trading 123 points lower (-0.5%). Merck's shares are down $1.83 (2.4%) while those of Home Depot have fallen $5.50 (2.3%), combining for a roughly 50-point drag on the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the decline are Chevron CVX, 1.04%, IBM IBM, 0.81%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.10%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the Dow results in a 6.86-point swing.

